data.chText: 相称的；成比例的；均衡的
data.enText: of an appropriate size, amount or degree in comparison with sth
Salary is proportional to years of experience.

data.chText: 与某事物成正比 / 反比
data.enText: to be directly/inversely proportional to sth

data.chText: 有子女家庭比无子女家庭的人均开销相对地少。
data.enText: Families with children spend proportionally less per person than families without children.

tr: one of the quantities in a mathematical proportion
properly related in size or degree or other measurable characteristics
example: the punishment ought to be proportional to the crime

value.def: If one amount is proportional to another, the two amounts increase and decrease at the same rate so there is always the same relationship between them.

example.ex: Loss of weight is directly proportional to the rate at which the disease is progressing.
example.tran: 体重的下降与病情发展的速度成正比。

example.ex: ...a proportional fee based on the final sale price.
example.tran: 与最后销售价格成比例的费用

example.ex: You have proportionally more fat on your thighs and hips than anywhere else on your body...
example.tran: 相应地，你的大腿和臀部的脂肪比身体其他部位要多。
候选人将按比例进行选举。

trans: 比例代表制(按参选各党派的得票比例分配席位)
